  <p>When I first moved to Palo Alto in 2013, I used to love going to the Stanford library.</p>

  <p>I'd go there to work, to read, to write, and sometimes just to think.</p>

  <p>Once, when I was exploring the stacks, I ended up in the dimly-lit basement level of the library - where I found a desk covered in graffiti from students who'd left notes written in pen.</p>

  <p>Some of them revealed the stress and anxiety of overwhelmed students who were overwhelmed. Others offered support and motivation.</p>

  <p>Altogether, they give a glimpse into the inner thoughts and feelings of college students in a high-pressure, high-performance environment.</p>

  <p>I read every single note on that desk, and recorded them for posterity. Hope you find them as thought-provoking as I did.</p>

