  <hr>

  <p>There was something raw and unsettling about the graffiti on that desk.</p>

  <p>I think it collectively expressed an unspoken truth shared by many students around the country. Things they'd never say out loud.</p>

  <p>A friend in Palo Alto once said to me:</p>

  <p><quote>"Stanford students are like swans. Calm and collected above the water, but kicking frantically under the water."</quote></p>

  <p>Obviously that's a generalization. But there's definitely some truth to it. And I think it equally applies to students at every prestigious, top-tier university.</p>

  <p>The notes on this desk give us a brief glimpse under the water.</p>
